A JOURNEY OF HOPE iN A TIME OF WAR.

( = WINNER = ) Audience Choice Award, Lake County Film Festival

( = WINNER = ) Best Documentary, Foursite Film Festival

Bonus Features: (preview) vimeo dawt com/user18032216/videos

* Extended Interviews with Martin Sheen, and M.C. Hammer
* Deleted Scene: Conspiracy
* Journal Excerpts

Starring:

Martin Sheen, Cindy Sheehan, Ron Kovic, M.C. Hammer,
Kristen &amp; Marshall Thompson, Ehren Watada

Official Selection at:

Vail Film Festival
Big Muddy Film Festival
Activating Human Rights Film Festival (AUS)
Non Violence International Film Festival (CAN)
Iris International Film Festival
Global Peace Film Festival
Foursite Film Festival
Lake County Film Festival
ReelHeart Film Festival (CAN)
Fallbrook Film Festival
Red Rock Film Festival

&quot;Inspiring and thought-provoking&quot; ~ Richard Propes, The Independent Critic

When Army Journalist Sgt. Marshall Thompson comes home from Iraq, one thing is clear to him: he must speak out against the war. With the help of his family, he sets off on a 500-mile peace walk through Utah, perhaps the most hawkish state in the nation, in hopes of changing perceptions about the war. Throughout his journey, he meets other peace-minded people, as well as those who are vehemently opposed to his efforts. Regardless of your views on the Iraq War, A Soldier's Peace will leave you with something to think about.

